summary: Workers at the General Motors Oshawa Assembly Complex will report for the final third shift tomorrow, as the company eliminates more than 700 direct jobs with hundreds of additional jobs lost at supply chain companies. headline: Lear T1XX program reports ‘negative’ for Magna, says UBS
summary: According to reports, Lear (LEA) has secured GM‘s (GM) T1XX program at Orion, with production starting in 2027, a result largely anticipated but not previously included in backlog, UBS tells investors in a research note. The win is neutral to slightly positive for Lear but negative for Magna (MGA), which previously operated the facility, the firm says. UBS has a Neutral rating and $135 price target on Lear shares.
